  "texts": [
    "Literacy is transformational.",
    "It reworks in the meaning of the world in the literate agent's image.Literacy in this view is a social process of participation in meaning: from representation as meaning for oneself; to communication as meaning made for others; to interpretation as the meaning one makes of the material traces of communication left by others (Fig. 2).",
    "The three are very different.",
    "Meaning for oneself is multimodal, a mixture of words, images, and embodied feelings.",
    "It takes context for granted."
